Answer.Res1: A space rover is launched when it is put into motion travels to outer space. The Chandrayaan-2 was launched in 2019, and it is currently the year 2023.  Therefore, The Chandrayaan-2 was launched 4 years ago.
Answer.Res2: The spacecraft's launch date is the month, day, and year that it begins its travel to outer space; and the spacecraft's oribital insertion is the day, month, and year that the vehicle's momentum or direction has to be changed.  The Chandrayaan-2's launch date was July 22, 2019, and its orbital insertion was August 20, 2019.  There are 31 days in the month of July.  Therefore, the Chandrayaan-2's Orbital insertion was held 29 days after its launch.
Answer.Res3: A rover's date for launch is the day, month, year that it starts traveling to outer space, and the landing date is the day, month, year that it returns to earth. The moon lander's launch date was July 22, 2019, and the moon lander's landing date was September 6, 2019.  There are 31 days in both the months of July and August.  Therefore, the moon lander's landing date was 46 days after the launch date.

Answer.Ans1: The Eastern and Western Christian traditions often celebrate Easter on different dates. The calculation of the date for Easter differs due to variations in the calendar systems and the methods used to determine the date.  If the Eastern and Western Easter dates happened in the same year, the number of days that would typically separate them is usually between 0 and 7 days. However, there have been instances where the Eastern and Western Easter dates have differed by more than a week.
Answer.Ans2: In 2021, the time between the Western and Eastern dates of Easter is approximately 28 days. The Western Easter was celebrated on April 2, while the Eastern Easter was celebrated on April 30.  In 2023, the time between the Western and Eastern dates of Easter is approximately 7 days. The Western Easter will be celebrated on April 7, while the Eastern Easter will be celebrated on April 14.  In 2024, the time between the Western and Eastern dates of Easter is approximately 35 days. The Western Easter will be celebrated on March 29, while the Eastern Easter will be celebrated on May 3.
Answer.Ans3: In 2024, Good Friday will be observed in the Eastern hemisphere on April 26th. The Eastern Easter will be celebrated on May 3rd, and Good Friday is traditionally observed two days before Easter Sunday.
Answer.Res1: The reason for the difference in Easter dates is primarily due to the use of different calendar systems. The Western Christian tradition follows the Gregorian calendar, while the Eastern Orthodox tradition follows the Julian calendar or a revised version of it. Additionally, each tradition has its own specific rules and calculations for determining the date of Easter based on lunar cycles and equinoxes.
Answer.Res2: The reason for the difference in the length of time between the Western and Eastern dates of Easter in different years is primarily due to the complex interplay of lunar cycles, equinoxes, and the different calendar systems used in each tradition. The Gregorian calendar used in the Western tradition and the Julian calendar or its revised version used in the Eastern tradition have different rules and calculations for determining the date of Easter. These variations in calendar systems and calculations result in differences in the timing of Easter between the Western and Eastern Christian traditions from year to year.

The Western tradition follows the Gregorian calendar, while the Eastern tradition follows the Julian calendar or its revised version. As a result, the dates of Good Friday can vary between the Western and Eastern hemispheres in any given year.
